text: Gisela Manns (born April 1942) is a former East German long track speed skater, who was active in the from 1956 to 1967. Manns represented her nation at the World Allround Speed Skating Championships for Women in 1963, finishing 32nd overall. She also competed at other international competitions. Between 1959 and 1964 she competed twelve times at the national Allround Championships, winning two overall silver medals and seven overall bronze medals. == Records== === Personal records === ==References== Category:1942 births Category:Place of birth missing (living people) Category:Date of birth missing (living people) Category:female speed skaters Category:East German sportswomen Category:Living people
